## SERP ANALYSIS

### Competitor Summary

- **Word count range:** 1,800–4,500 words (avg: ~2,800); heavy image-to-text ratio — most content is gallery-style with short descriptive blurbs per design
- **Common H2 topics across top 10 pages:**
  1. Floral nail art designs (hibiscus, daisy, 3D blooms)
  2. Fruit nail art (watermelon, strawberry, lemon, citrus, cherry)
  3. Beach / ocean-themed nail art
  4. 3D nail art and textured designs
  5. French tip variations (coloured, reverse, floral-tipped)
  6. Chrome and metallic nail art
  7. Watercolour / aura nails
  8. Tropical and vacation-inspired designs
  9. Mediterranean / tile-inspired art
  10. Minimalist vs maximalist approaches
  11. Nail art by nail length (short vs long)
  12. DIY tips / tools for nail art at home

- **Content approach:** Competitors run listicle-gallery formats — numbered designs with 1–3 sentence descriptions and a product or tool note. Most mix aspirational language with light technique guidance. Very few address skill-level filtering or durability of art in summer conditions (heat, water, sunscreen).

- **Visual patterns:** 15–30 images standard; some pages hit 40+. Each design gets its own image. Video embeds rare (1–2 max). Pinterest-optimised vertical images dominate.

### Our Strategic Approach

- **Differentiation:** Organise by art *theme* (florals, fruits, beach) rather than a flat numbered list — readers can navigate to their vibe instead of scrolling 50 designs. Layer in a brief skill-level tag (beginner / intermediate / nail-tech territory) per design cluster so users self-select. No competitor addresses summer-specific durability of nail art (heat, chlorine, saltwater) — we own that angle.
- **Structure plan:** Three clear theme pillars (Floral → Fruit → Beach) with a bonus section on 2026's breakout techniques (3D sculpting, watercolour, Mediterranean tile). Internal linking woven into theme transitions rather than bolted on at the end.
- **Tone direction:** Warm editorial voice — editorial authority of a beauty magazine, accessibility of a best friend who gets nails.

