## USER RESEARCH

### Top 5 Pain Points

1. **Nail art chipping or lifting within days** — especially frustrating in summer; heat, swimming, sunscreen, and frequent hand-washing all accelerate breakdown; users feel they wasted time and money.
2. **Can't recreate inspo photos at home** — pinned designs look achievable but require specialised tools (sculpting gel, nail art brushes, dotting tools) that most users don't own; disappointment gap is high.
3. **Overwhelm from too many options** — searching "summer nail art" returns hundreds of designs with no filtering by skill level, nail length, or occasion; users don't know where to start.
4. **Designs look good online but wrong IRL** — colours photograph differently; some art styles (especially 3D florals) don't translate well to shorter or natural nails; readers feel misled.
5. **No guidance on durability** — inspirational posts show beautiful art but never address whether a design will survive a beach holiday, chlorine pool, or summer heat; users discover too late that some art techniques need professional gel systems to last.

### User Sentiment
Excited and aspirational, but frequently disappointed by the gap between pinned inspo and real-world results — especially around skill level and longevity.

