## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

- **Recommended Voice:** Warm editorial expert — the knowledgeable friend who works at a beauty magazine and actually gets manicures
- **Tone Characteristics:**
  - Enthusiastic but never breathless — no "OMG you NEED this"
  - Specific and descriptive — paint the visual clearly in words, don't just say "stunning"
  - Empowering not gatekeeping — skill-level honesty without discouraging beginners
  - Seasonally grounded — references real summer scenarios (beach holiday, festival, garden party)
  - Confident editorial pace — medium-short sentences, no filler
- **Language Style:** Direct second-person ("your nails", "you'll want"); British English spelling throughout; avoid jargon without explanation; lean into sensory and visual language
- **Audience Match:** Target reader is browsing at leisure, saving for later — she wants to feel inspired not lectured; voice should match the energy of a Pinterest board brought to life in prose

